We recommended and the City Mayor agreed to direct the:
a. Inventory Committee to complete the physical count of the PPE including the identification of ongoing projects recorded under the CIP accounts and determination of non-existing PPE or Infrastructure Projects; 
b. City Engineering Office (CEO) to coordinate with the City Accounting Office the status of the CIP projects for determination whether there are completed projects from prior years and not transferred to the appropriate PPE accounts; 
c. City Accountant to:
c.1 Take up the necessary entries to adjust the PPE and CIP accounts based on the Certificates of Project Completion and Acceptance submitted by the CEO, if any; and
c.2 Drop the unreconciled lumped amounts of CIP accounts carrying beginning balances without available details from the books of accounts, if warranted.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to:
1. Conduct immediate reconciliation of records and make the necessary adjustments to correct the balances Real Property Tax Receivable and Special Education Tax Receivable and submit to the audit team the approved JEV together with its supporting documents including the working papers. Treasurer should provide a complete list of taxpayers and the corresponding amount of uncollected delinquent taxes necessary for the establishment of the subsidiary ledgers;
2. Undertake periodic reconciliation of records to ensure correct and reliable balances.

We recommended that Management:

1. Allocate budget for the training needs of the GFPS on GAD planning and budgeting and the use of GAD tools like HGDG;

2. Ensure consistency of data among its GAD reports and ensure that changes in the GPB be properly communicated with the DILG Regional Office pursuant to Item C.7.2 of the JMC 2013-01, as amended;

3. Direct the GFPS to refer to the Annexes D and E of the aforecited JMC in properly filling out the GPB and GDAR forms.

We recommended that Management:
Allocate budget for the training needs of the GFPS on GAD planning and budgeting and the use of GAD tools like HGDG;
Ensure consistency of data among its GAD reports and ensure that changes in the GPB be properly communicated with the DILG Regional Office pursuant to Item C.7.2 of the JMC 2013-01, as amended;
