Require retiring accountable official or employee to undertake an authorization (in affidavit form) to deduct financial obligations including unliquidated cash advance from the terminal leave benefits pursuant to 5.13 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012;

Require officials and employees who intend to transfer to another office to liquidate their cash advance before Clearance from Property and Money Accountabilities is released to ensure settlement of accounts; 

Assign personnel in the Accounting Office who will closely monitor the movement of the long outstanding cash advances and to prepare quarterly report copy furnished the Auditor; 

Review the accounts of Ms. Emnace and determine whether her unliquidated cash advances can be deducted from her terminal leave claim/collectible from the City; and

Require the Officials who signed the clearance of retiring personnel with unsettled cash advances to be jointly responsible in paying the outstanding cash advances of the said retired personnel.

